OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 19 May to Thu 28 May
OL,6,FChangeable conditions look to dominate
OL,7,Fat first, with low pressure often
OL,8,Fclose by. This means periods of rain
OL,9,For showers, some of which could be
OL,10,Fheavy and more focussed across
OL,11,Fnorthwestern areas. Drier interludes
OL,12,Fare also expected, most especially
OL,13,Facross southeastern UK. As this period
OL,14,Fprogresses, high pressure is likely to
OL,15,Fbegin to build from the south bringing
OL,16,Fmore settled weather, although with
OL,17,Foccasional showers. Temperatures near-
OL,18,Fnormal to begin, but tending to rise
OL,19,Fas the period progresses, perhaps
OL,20,Fbecoming rather warm by the end of the
OL,21,Fperiod, especially in the south. Winds
OL,22,Fwill be stronger during the first part
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fof the period, generally from a
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fsouthwesterly direction, before
OL,25,Fbecoming lighter in line with the more
OL,26,Fsettled conditions.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1778764275
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 28 May to Thu 11 Jun
OL,6,FPatterns which bring more settled
OL,7,Fweather are more likely to dominate
OL,8,Ftowards the end of May. Whilst further
OL,9,Frain and showers are possible at
OL,10,Ftimes, there is likely to be longer
OL,11,Fspells of fine and dry weather. Into
OL,12,FJune, more mixed conditions are likely
OL,13,Fwith spells of rain and showers, but
OL,14,Falso some drier weather at times.
OL,15,FTemperatures are most likely to be
OL,16,Fnear or slightly above average
OL,17,Foverall, with some warm weather
OL,18,Fpossible at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
